<body>
<segment id="1" parent="1001" relname="preparation">Find a Contractor</segment>
<segment id="2" parent="1002" relname="preparation">Even the handiest of homeowners need assistance with renovations occasionally .</segment>
<segment id="3" parent="1003" relname="preparation">From new construction to tear downs ,</segment>
<segment id="4" parent="1005" relname="span">help from an expert may be needed</segment>
<segment id="5" parent="4" relname="purpose">to ensure the job gets completed correctly .</segment>
<segment id="6" parent="1007" relname="span">Before calling the first name</segment>
<segment id="7" parent="6" relname="elaboration">you come across in your phone book or on the Internet ,</segment>
<segment id="8" parent="1008" relname="span">consider the following advice</segment>
<segment id="9" parent="8" relname="circumstance">when trying to find a contractor .</segment>
<segment id="10" parent="1010" relname="preparation">Steps</segment>
<segment id="11" parent="1010" relname="joint">Seek advice from family and friends .</segment>
<segment id="12" parent="1013" relname="span">Ask people</segment>
<segment id="13" parent="1014" relname="joint">you know</segment>
<segment id="14" parent="1015" relname="span">and trust for a recommendation</segment>
<segment id="15" parent="14" relname="condition">if they have had similar work done in their homes .</segment>
<segment id="16" parent="1017" relname="span">You will feel more confident</segment>
<segment id="17" parent="1018" relname="span">in calling a contractor</segment>
<segment id="18" parent="17" relname="elaboration">who has made your best friend or brother happy with the renovation .</segment>
<segment id="19" parent="1020" relname="span">Consult with professionals</segment>
<segment id="20" parent="19" relname="elaboration">you already know .</segment>
<segment id="21" parent="1023" relname="condition">If you have a great electrician or plumber ,</segment>
<segment id="22" parent="1023" relname="joint">he has experience with reliable contractors</segment>
<segment id="23" parent="1023" relname="joint">and will not hesitate to provide you with names and numbers .</segment>
<segment id="24" parent="1025" relname="span">Your professional will not recommend someone</segment>
<segment id="25" parent="24" relname="elaboration">he would n&apos;t use .</segment>
<segment id="26" parent="1010" relname="joint">Collect more than one contractor estimate .</segment>
<segment id="27" parent="1028" relname="span">Make sure that you have at least 3 contractors bid on your home renovation project</segment>
<segment id="28" parent="1029" relname="span">rather than hiring the first one</segment>
<segment id="29" parent="28" relname="elaboration">that walks through your front door .</segment>
<segment id="30" parent="1032" relname="span">When you sit down</segment>
<segment id="31" parent="30" relname="purpose">to compare ,</segment>
<segment id="32" parent="1033" relname="span">the work</segment>
<segment id="33" parent="32" relname="elaboration">that was quoted by each contractor should be similar in its specifications .</segment>
<segment id="34" parent="1035" relname="preparation">Examine business cards .</segment>
<segment id="35" parent="1036" relname="span">A contractor should provide a business card</segment>
<segment id="36" parent="1037" relname="joint">when meeting you ,</segment>
<segment id="37" parent="1037" relname="joint">and that card needs to have a physical address , telephone number and a license number .</segment>
<segment id="38" parent="39" relname="circumstance">Once she leaves ,</segment>
<segment id="39" parent="1039" relname="span">verify the information and the status of her license .</segment>
<segment id="40" parent="1041" relname="preparation">Check references .</segment>
<segment id="41" parent="1041" relname="joint">A decent contractor will not hesitate to provide a written list of references ,</segment>
<segment id="42" parent="1043" relname="span">and the longer the list ,</segment>
<segment id="43" parent="42" relname="elaboration">the more likely he is reputable .</segment>
<segment id="44" parent="1045" relname="span">Call as many on the list</segment>
<segment id="45" parent="1046" relname="span">until you have the information</segment>
<segment id="46" parent="45" relname="elaboration">you need .</segment>
<segment id="47" parent="1048" relname="span">A tip</segment>
<segment id="48" parent="1049" relname="span">to ensure quality is to skip around the list</segment>
<segment id="49" parent="1050" relname="span">instead of going in the order</segment>
<segment id="50" parent="49" relname="elaboration">provided .</segment>
<segment id="51" parent="1052" relname="preparation">Verify insurance information .</segment>
<segment id="52" parent="53" relname="condition">When you are meeting with a prospective contractor ,</segment>
<segment id="53" parent="1053" relname="span">ask her to show you an insurance certificate .</segment>
<segment id="54" parent="1054" relname="span">In the alternative , you can request the contractor &apos;s insurance carrier and telephone number</segment>
<segment id="55" parent="56" relname="attribution">so that you can be sure</segment>
<segment id="56" parent="1055" relname="span">the policy is in good standing .</segment>
<segment id="57" parent="1057" relname="preparation">Warnings</segment>
<segment id="58" parent="1058" relname="preparation">Beware of cash .</segment>
<segment id="59" parent="1060" relname="span">When you find a contractor</segment>
<segment id="60" parent="59" relname="elaboration">that you like ,</segment>
<segment id="61" parent="1059" relname="span">ask how he expects to be paid .</segment>
<segment id="62" parent="1062" relname="span">The one</segment>
<segment id="63" parent="1063" relname="span">who wants all cash may be cutting corners</segment>
<segment id="64" parent="1064" relname="span">that will also cut the quality of the job</segment>
<segment id="65" parent="64" relname="elaboration">done in your home .</segment>
<segment id="66" parent="1065" relname="sequence">Drop a contractor without a cell phone .</segment>
<segment id="67" parent="1067" relname="span">Almost every professional has a cell phone ,</segment>
<segment id="68" parent="69" relname="condition">so if you find a contractor without one ,</segment>
<segment id="69" parent="1068" relname="span">do not hire her .</segment>
<segment id="70" parent="1070" relname="span">A contractor should provide you with means</segment>
<segment id="71" parent="70" relname="purpose">to reach her easily .</segment>
<segment id="72" parent="1072" relname="span">Question the contractor</segment>
<segment id="73" parent="72" relname="elaboration">who eliminates the permit .</segment>
<segment id="74" parent="75" relname="condition">If your renovation project is substantial ,</segment>
<segment id="75" parent="1074" relname="span">you will most likely need a construction permit .</segment>
<segment id="76" parent="1076" relname="condition">If the contractor suggests skipping this paperwork ,</segment>
<segment id="77" parent="1076" relname="contrast">it could mean that he is n&apos;t licensed</segment>
<segment id="78" parent="1076" relname="contrast">or does n&apos;t want to be monitored .</segment>
